Find Eventual Safe States

Given a directed graph, return all nodes that are safe.
A node is called safe if:
    Starting from that node,
    every possible path eventually ends
    at a terminal node.

A terminal node means: Node with no outgoing edges
Example

Edges:
    {0,1}
    {1,2}
    {2,3}
    {3,1}
    {4,5}

Graph:
    0 → 1
    1 → 2
    2 → 3
    3 → 1
    4 → 5
    5
    6

Step 1: Find Cycle
  Look carefully: 1 → 2 → 3 → 1
  This is a cycle.
  So:
    1 unsafe
    2 unsafe
    3 unsafe
    
Step 2: Node reaching cycle also unsafe
  0 → 1
  Since 1 enters cycle,
  0 can also loop forever.

So: 0 unsafe

 Step 3: Safe Nodes
    4 → 5
    5 is terminal.

Every path from 4 ends safely.
So:
  4 safe
  5 safe
Node 6 has no edges.
So:6 safe
Final answer:[4,5,6]

Main Logic

We use:

DFS + Cycle Detection
Idea:
  If a node can reach a cycle,
  it is unsafe.
  Else safe.

Arrays Used
1. vis[]
  Already visited node
  Avoid repeated DFS.

2. pathVis[]
    Node currently in DFS path
    Used to detect cycle.

3. safe[]
Stores whether node is safe

class Solution {
    public ArrayList<Integer> safeNodes(int V, int[][] edges) {
        // Code here
        
        List<List<Integer>> graph=  new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=0; i<V; i++){
            graph.add(new ArrayList<>());
        }
        
        for(int[] e: edges){
            int u=e[0];
            int v=e[1];
            graph.get(u).add(v);
        }
        boolean[] vis = new boolean[V];
        boolean[] pathVis= new boolean[V];
        boolean[] safe = new boolean[V];
        
        for(int i=0; i< V; i++){
            
            if(!vis[i]){
                dfs(i, graph, vis,pathVis,safe);
            }
        }
        
        ArrayList<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        
        for(int i=0; i<V; i++){
            
            if(safe[i]){
                ans.add(i);
            }
        }
        
        return ans;
    }
    
    static boolean dfs (int i, List<List<Integer>> graph, boolean[] vis,
            boolean[] pathVis, boolean[] safe){
                vis[i]=true;
                pathVis[i]=true;
                
                for(int nei: graph.get(i)){
                    
                    if(!vis[nei]){
                        if(dfs(nei,graph,vis,pathVis,safe)){
                            return true;
                        }
                    }
                    else if(pathVis[nei]){
                        return true;
                        
                    }
                }
                pathVis[i] =false;
                safe[i]=true;
                return false;
                
            }
}
